town_website_description: Ayer is a thriving town in the historic Nashoba Valley of Massachusetts. It is located 35 miles northwest of Boston, and within easy access of Interstate 495 and State Route 2. Montachusett Regional Transit Authority (MART) supplies Councils-On-Aging service. Commuter rail service from Boston's North Station is provided by the MBTA with a stop in Ayer on its Fitchburg Line. Ayer contains routes 2A, 110, and 111. Ayer is only one town away from both Interstate 495 and Route 2.The town is proud of their diversity, safe and beautiful neighborhoods, excellent schools, strong links to the railroad and Devens, quaint downtown, appreciation and protection of our natural resources, and our focus on the well-being of families and the community.

town_website_description: Harvard is a well preserved rural community with an interesting history. Situated in Worcester County, Harvard is 32 miles west of Boston, and 22 miles northeast of Worcester. Routes 2 and 495 run through the town, and the Nashua River forms its western boundary. Today it is an affluent residential town noted for its excellent public schools, with its students consistently ranking in the state's top ten test results in English and math.
